Set in a thick plaque with matching iron trim, its simplicity in form is what gives it such sophistication. Also available in rectangular form (6479). Antique mirror finish may vary.

A symbol of the sun setting over the desert horizon as it fades into the night. The Horizon Mirror features an intriguing oblong shape, antique nickel finished brass frame and antique smoke mirror. Antiquing is hand-applied and will vary. It hangs sturdy and flush to the wall using a security cleat mount.

This round cocktail table perfectly represents the essence of artisan design and craftsmanship. First, note the unique texture of the hand-hammered top, and then the solid iron bar that has been hand-forged into a curvaceous knot detail on each leg. The natural iron finish keeps it simple and reinforces the organic nature of the design. Round cocktail tables are inviting and without the sharp corners are children and pet friendly.

Richly applied brushstrokes in a brilliant chemical oxidation creates the Modernist Art aesthetic of this bold mirror. To create the tonal variance, artisans apply the textures by hand in layers, then leaving the organic chemical processes to do the rest—making each mirror unique. Its round, unframed structure makes a minimalist statement, so this mirror transcends singular style to fit in just about anywhere, whether paired over a vanity or displayed above a console.

The dark and moody border of this bold mirror was inspired by the antiqued distressing of our Luxembourg Mirrors. The mirror tiles that form the border get their intensity from a handmade process that involves applying a finish that then undergoes a chemical reaction. Once completed, the result is a nearly opaque surface that’s rich with organic texture beneath the glass surface. The plain glass mirror in the center makes this version more functional than its decorative counterpart.
Zephyr Bench

No doubt this mirror was geometric inspired—it’s a wonderful combination of simple squares, rectangles and a central circle, all delicately trimmed in a polished nickel finish Each mirror is clear and features a bevel edge that elevates the look immensely. Can be hung vertically or horizontally for versatility. Hangs on a security cleat attachment. Also available in antique brass (2198).

Individual iron rods are welded together and finished in silver leaf to create this fresh interpretation of the French-inspired starburst design. The round shape looks great alone or in multiples. Hung with security cleat attachment. Silver leaf finish may vary. Also available in antiqued gold leaf (2134).

This elegant ovoid mirror is held in place by an organic cluster of antique brass leafy branches that conceal a small ledge at the plain mirror's base. Perfect for a scented candle, figurine or objet d'art. Use it over a console or in a glamorous powder room. Hung with a security cleat attachment.
This cast iron whimsical dining table base is shaped like tree branches. A large round clear glass top rests on top of the base. Also available with 48," 54," and 66" glass.

Hovering ever-so-slightly against the wall, this brilliant mirror performs “depth-defying” feats in a space. Two polished nickel brackets hold a plain glass mirror, which has rounded edges for a softer look. Can be hung vertically or horizontally depending on the wall space. Hangs on two security cleat attachments. Also available in antique brass (6872).

A truly one-of-a-kind piece, the Jude Mirror's starburst-patterned antiquing amidst a convex mirror draws attention from all angles. Also available in small (2865) and medium (4104). Feature a security cleat attachment. Finishes may vary.

The Hana Mirror is highlighted by its antiqued mirror border that gives way to a plain mirrored surface. Contrasting mirror finishes are accentuated by antique brass details and gold painted wooden frame. Can be hung horizontally or vertically. Features security cleat attachement. Finish may vary.

The more practical relative of the antique dragon etched counterpart, this mirror, still held in place by dramatic antique brass talons, is left clear in the center and framed with a smoky, irregular rim of antiqued mirror. Perfect in a chic powder room or in pairs over small consoles or cabinets. Features a security cleat attachment. Can be hung vertically or horizontally. Also available in antiqued dragon etched (DD2084). Finish may vary.

Why mount your favorite treasure when it can float? Windsor Smith transformed a classical pedestal shelf into illusionistic display using a clear acrylic top. Smoky gray lacquer resin completes its modern transformation. Lovely paired with our Larissa urn or your own collected treasures, this piece bridges all styles of interiors.

This mirror is the design equivalent to adding diamonds to wear with your evening gown. Its pure and classic elegance is what makes it stunning, with details including an antique brass finish, refined beaded trim and etched line carvings. This beauty hangs both vertically or diagonally to fit the look you’re aiming for. Mirror is trimmed with a bevel edge. Hangs on a security cleat attachment. Also comes in vintage silver (6871).

Featuring a frame of alternating rippled antiqued mirrored glass tiles, the Isabel Square Mirror is a subtle, softened industrial piece of decor. With a beveled mirror and textured panel frame, Isabel is an easy way to add layers and depth to a space. Hung with security cleat attachment. Rectangular mirror (2944) also available. Finish may vary.

Round cocktail tables are the perfect choice if you have children or a tendency to run into corners. This natural iron cocktail table features round edges and an acid-etched top that resembles the cross cut of a tree trunk.

A traditional window-frame form with an artisan-crafted accent. The Henrietta Mirror features a distressed painted rust frame encasing multiple panels of antiqued mirror. A striking fleur-de-lis etched pattern adorns the outer mirror pieces. Can be hung vertically or horizontally. Features a security cleat attachment. Finish may vary.

The Humphrie Lamp is tumbled industrial design personified. A multifaceted lesson in geometry, the soft silver finished Humphrie screams space-age sheen. The design is brought together with its rectangular off-white linen shade lined in matching cotton, and matching finial.

The pivots on each of the five, clear seedy globes can be adjusted to suit your needs and design aesthetic. With an undulating design and vintage silver finish, the piece itself is an arresting light sculpture - perfect for hanging horizontally, vertically or even as a ceiling mount. Shown here with clear tubular bulbs, the piece is damp rated and approved for use in covered outdoor areas.

The beauty of handcrafted ceramic joins forces with modern design to create this serene table lamp. The muted, shadow gray reactive glaze accentuates the ribbed details in the neck, as well as adding brushstroke texture to the globular base—evidence to its handcrafted nature. Topped with an ivory linen drum shade with ivory cotton lining and an acrylic ball finial. Glaze finish may vary.

Arboreal in form and richly organic in so many ways, this pendant is quite fascinating. An exaggerated patina is created by hand using a verdigris finish, so it almost looks like a 19th-century French antique. Even the immaculate details in the iron are done by hand. Encased in glass, six sockets fit chandelier bulbs to polish the look. Verdigris finish may vary.

A unique design that fools the eye, this piece is inspired by our popular, more rectangular Autero Mirror (DD2004). The spike holding the mirror appears to have been hammered into the wall, when in fact, the piece is actually suspended from a cleat on the mirror’s back, so it is purely decorative. The iron frame has intensely etched texturing and is finished in burnt wax, surrounding a flat mirror. Also available in a larger version (DD2614).

Clean, subdued and timeless, the London Pendant's opal glass cylindrical shade is caged by antique brass-finished steel framing and finished off with a delicate matching finial detail. Additional pipe available (PIPE-101). Also available in vintage silver (42161). Approved for use in covered outdoor areas.

The subtle grooved surface pattern on this porcelain table lamp adds a dimensionality that is further enhanced when the hand applied blue wash glaze is applied over the ivory crackle finish. The euro-taper shade is constructed of ivory microfiber and perfectly balances the base. This is a classic silhouette with an artful abstract pattern making it new.

This table lamp is designed in the likeness of an Art Deco candlestick, with its own class and sophistication to boot. Crafted from iron, it’s slender, tapered and just a little geometric, exuding so much style—especially due to the verdigris finish, which gives it a lovely faux patina. Antique brass finish accents only add to its allure. Topped with a drum shade in beige linen with ivory cotton lining and matching brass ball finial.

Who knew that leather and metal could make such a sophisticated pairing? Brushed brass forms the structure, cognac leather wraps it, stitched together with an exposed hem to add a handsome finishing touch. Topped with a tapered, white linen barrel shade with a cotton lining and matching brass ball finial. Also comes in indigo leather (DC12013), as well as a floor lamp version in cognac leather (DC72014) and indigo leather (DC72015). Leather finish may vary.

A relative of the Ferris, the Foley Lamp offers another take on the transparency trend. The smoke crystal is subtle enough to play nicely with any other finish or color. The barely-there crystal discs are accented by the vintage silver pipe and ash microfiber drum shade. Features a matching crystal finial.
Gilda Vase

The raw look of jute rope fully wraps the stem of this slender table lamp. Natural fibers give the design an organic edge and an incredible amount of texture you can see and feel. It’s mounted in a plate of walnut finished wood, which helps conceal the clear cord for a streamlined look. Topped with a tapered drum, slip uno fitter shade in ivory linen with ivory cotton lining. Also available as a floor lamp (DC79000).

The secret to this lovely, ethereal piece lies in a single, clear crystal ball foot that looks to seemingly suspend the end of bowl in midair. Lustrous brass is the perfect counterpoint to crystal, accentuating the sculptural effects of its organic, sensual shape. Use it for jewel-like effect as a catchall on a cocktail or side table, entry table, or dressing vanity.
Wide curling brass ribbons in a rose gold finish come together to create interpretive table sculpture on a white marble base.
Jensen Magnifying Object

Our variant on the monumental urn is modernized and unadorned, allowing eyes to focus on its unique form and finish. Super slim handles and a thin tablet plinth set off a smooth, lustrous brass exterior, while contrasting hammered brass dresses its interior.

Add panache to the powder room or create an elegant bar with several of these functional and decorative clear glass bottle decanters. Each bottle features a leather collar bound by brass brads. Food safe.

Who knew that leather and metal could make such a sophisticated pairing? Brushed brass forms the structure, cognac leather wraps it, stitched together with an exposed hem to add a handsome finishing touch. Topped with a tapered, white linen barrel shade with a cotton lining and matching brass ball finial. Also comes in indigo leather (DC72015), as well as a table lamp version in cognac leather (DC12012) and indigo leather (DC12012). Leather finish may vary.

Inspiration can come from the wildest places. Crafted thoughtfully to look just like a true gazelle horn, this sculpture is an almost identical replica, with a natural finish that accentuates all the details. Up close you can see grooves and markings that have been artistically recreated for lifelike detail. Mounted to an inch-thick piece of cut crystal, it stands majestically at over two feet tall. Finish may vary. Also comes in an antique brass finish (9554).

Smooth cuts create the supple ribbed textures in this glass centerpiece. The blend of matte and glossy finishes heightens the look, formed in smoky tobacco colored glass for even more luxury. Though it is made to fulfill a variety of purposes, it captures beauty even on its own. Also comes as a vase (6898).

Smooth cuts create the supple ribbed textures in this glass vase. The blend of matte and glossy finishes heightens the look, formed in smoky tobacco colored glass for even more luxury. Though it is made to fulfill a variety of purposes, it captures beauty even on its own. Also comes as a centerpiece (6899)
Riya Container

Create a modern statement with this signature iron sphere sculpture made of square bar stock and finished in gold leaf. Place a single one on top of a stack of books, or buy all the versions and fill a bowl. Available in two sizes and two finishes (burnt wax iron and gold leaf).

Category: Tables\Accent, Side, End and Occassional Tables
ItemDescription: Our Vickers Side Table is a paradigm for natural sophistication. A thin piece of rattan pole is wrapped continuously around the polyresin frame to create the hourglass shape. The top features an antique brass disk inlay that adds a striking yet subtle element to the natural finish of this organic piece. Crafted from naturally durable materials, this side table is also quite steady so adding a glass top is optional but not necessary for function. Rattan may vary slightly in color.

Category: Tables\Accent, Side, End and Occassional Tables
ItemDescription: This exquisite end table is like bringing the brilliance of the sun into a space. Honed hexagonal white marble is inlaid with 30 slices of polished brass, forming a shining sunburst design that is elegant and oh-so-sophisticated. It’s truly a feat of daring craftsmanship. The six-leg base is smithed from iron and finished in an antique brass finish, with a silhouette that has a slightly Moroccan feel. Also available as a cocktail table (6881). Marble tones may vary.

Grand curvatures and modern gray tones make for an inspiring place to work. The frame is coated in an exclusive, charcoal lacquer, rounded to give the desk a uniquely updated design. On the wide work space is a lacy and light, tropical ofram wood ven eer in chateau gray, laid with a slip matched technique where the slices are patterned in the same way, rather than alternating. In keeping the façade clean and sleek, the drawer features a recessed handle, with single extension, soft-close glides.

Category: Accent Furniture\Occasional, Side and End Tables
ItemDescription: Classic white marble and sleek polished stainless steel make for a sophisticated pairing in this modern side table. The slab of natural marble rests effortlessly within the frame and is supported underneath by a full perimeter of steel. Also comes in dark natural iron with white marble (6392) and vintage brass with black marble (6683). Marble tones may vary.

Serve your guests without forfeiting function or style. Crafted with an iron frame in an antique brass finish, each of the three tiers of this capsule-shaped bar cart features a different element. The top tier is inset with solid white marble, the second tier is inset with clear glass and the third tier is inset with mirrored glass. The use of mixed materials delivers a luxe visual appeal. Finish may vary.
Your barware and accouterments will shine on this swanky bar cart. The x-frame features a mix of contrasting materials including polished nickel steel, natural teak and clear glass. Finish may vary.

Category: Accent Furniture\Occasional, Side and End Tables
ItemDescription: Sleek. Simple. Sophisticated. This table is modern elegance realized. Seamlessly crafted in stainless steel, it is finished in a polished nickel finish, yet with slightly natural touches that recall a sort of Japanese Wabi-Sabi balance. Two tiers of shelving are plated in beveled mirror glass to not only elevate the look even further, but to add light and shine. Pairs with the Marcus Cocktail Table (6912) and Marcus Console (6909).

Category: Tables\Accent, Side, End and Occassional Tables
ItemDescription: Organic style with an eclectic edge; this iron table supported by cast tree branches is finished in a distressed silver.

Natural driftwood and a large glass top unite to form this artistic testament to nature's aesthetic features. A dramatic visual focal point for a dining space, each is a unique and one-of-a-kind piece sculpted by Mother Nature herself. The rustic form of the naturally sculpted base features a weathered, whitewash finish that will fit seamlessly with existing coastal décor. Due to the organic nature, size and shape of wood may vary. 72" glass top available.

We took the ever-popular design of our Celeste Accent Table and updated it with a solid white marble top and base and a fixed-position black iron leg, to create this pub table version. The beveled edges of the marble top add depth to the slight veining that moves freely across the surface. Though larger in size, this table has a small footprint like its predecessor, making it a great piece for small space.

Category: Tables\Accent, Side, End and Occassional Tables
ItemDescription: Our Vlad Side Table puts forth the best of contemporary and modern ivory lacquer design. The smooth round top is complemented by the stark but curved lines that compose the pedestal-style base. Sculptural in form and functional by design, this piece works just as well as a striking sofa companion as it does an architectural accent all on its own. The versatile color allows this side table to perform in various décor styles.

Category: Tables\Accent, Side, End and Occassional Tables
ItemDescription: If you’ve been scouting for a perflectly charming piece for your space, you’re in luck. This cleverly crafted stool is petite, but full of character. At bird’s eye view, you can see the stem and four-leaf design as well as the warm Sahara finish. From the side, dissected blocks of wood reveal rich wood grain and natural knots that really make it unique. Doubles as a seat or small side table. Finish may vary.

The rustic form of the naturally sculpted base features a weathered, whitewash finish that will fit seamlessly with existing coastal décor. Due to the organic nature, size and shape of wood may vary. 66" glass top available.

A larger version of our Kamile Side Table, this pub-style stand has mastered the elements of mixed materials. A smoke gray stain adds a distressed feel to the solid oak, while the natural iron accents lend an industrial touch. A natural iron ring under the table top matches the iron base, which delivers a cohesiveness throughout this piece and creates additional support.

Category: Accent Furniture\Occasional, Side and End Tables
ItemDescription: Richland Side Table

An intricate web is the defining element in this dining table. Natural iron square tubes are hand welded together to create the base of this table. Therefore no two will ever be the same. A large round clear glass top rests on top of the base. Also available with 54", 60", and 66" glass.

This 60" dining table is made of solid wood which has been waxed to maintain the natural color. The top has been clad in galvanized steel and attached with small nail heads in a circular pattern. Perfect dining table or as a striking entry piece.

Category: Tables\Accent, Side, End and Occassional Tables
ItemDescription: Inspired by the rounded, gourd-shaped tribal drums found throughout Africa, this side table has a silhouette that is voluptuous and curvy. It’s crafted from blackened wood, which is first sandblasted to give it an intense, charred wood finish that you can really see and feel. The top has an added brushed texture that is so unique, and the overall slightly glossy look comes from the final wax coat that’s added to give it modern polish.

Category: Tables\Accent, Side, End and Occassional Tables
ItemDescription: Diminutive in scale, this aluminum accent table is cast in a deep bronze finish. A dueling antiqued aluminum finish was applied to the inner curves for slight contrast. Layer with a larger end table for a nesting effect. Finish may vary.

Category: Tables\Accent, Side, End and Occassional Tables
ItemDescription: We love the yin and yang on this transitional side table. Hand-forged black iron legs are delicately tapered creating the perfect base for the chunky white marble top. Also available as a cocktail table (4392). Marble may vary.

Category: Tables\Accent, Side, End and Occassional Tables
ItemDescription: Made with a faux bois inspiration in mind, this side table is ideal for a space that needs a little natural beauty. Though it’s cast from aluminum, it’s molded into an exaggerated woodgrain design to give it an organic sophistication. The shape is what gives it a modern update, tapered at the base and in the top with a narrowed collar that joins them together. The form alone recalls Brancusi style. The entire piece has a graphite finish, giving it that bit of mood we love.

Category: Tables\Accent, Side, End and Occassional Tables
ItemDescription: We love the yin and yang on this transitional side table. Hand-forged black iron legs are delicately tapered creating the perfect base for the chunky white marble top. Also available as an accent table (4391) and a cocktail table (4392). Marble color may vary.

Category: Tables\Accent, Side, End and Occassional Tables
ItemDescription: Industrial materials and hand-applied techniques update the classic shape of this enviable end table. The chiseled white marble top sits atop a pedestal base with fanned black iron rods. Marble may vary.

Category: Tables\Accent, Side, End and Occassional Tables
ItemDescription: This seemingly simple table has details that make it quite extraordinary. It is crafted entirely from cast aluminum, finished in a graphite tone that gives it a slightly Brutalist and tribal look, though updated in a polished, modern silhouette. The legs are thinly tapered to accentuate the aesthetic, with an outer arch—a detail common in Art Nouveau tables. It’s scaled to fit in a variety of spaces in a variety of different ways.

Category: Tables\Accent, Side, End and Occassional Tables
ItemDescription: Beauty unfolds at every curve on this traditional oak side table. Smooth cut-outs reveal a cinched silhouette that is as alluring as the deep ebony stain. Prop a decorative box or sculpture on the middle shelf to create another styling moment. Nylon nail-in glides will protect exposed floors.

Category: Tables\Accent, Side, End and Occassional Tables
ItemDescription: Cylindrical with a twist, the Herschel Side Table is an iron, bronze-finished beauty that instantly adds weight and artisanal detail to any space. The hammered finish brings unexpectedness to the table's modified hourglass form. Matching cocktail table (2824) and lamp (42069-622) also available.

Category: Tables\Accent, Side, End and Occassional Tables
ItemDescription: A smaller version of our Hattie End Table (4257), this “C” shaped side table features an antiqued mirror top combined with blackened iron legs. A striking shape, this piece fits perfectly next to a chair or can become a unique nightstand. Mirror finish may vary.

Category: Tables\Accent, Side, End and Occassional Tables
ItemDescription: The Grayson Side Table takes a classic shape and turns it on its head.The natural iron frame features intentional ridges that lend a rawness to the timeless design. As for the tabletop, we've deemed this blend 'Cosmic' Marble, a unique material with natural veining that moves fluidly between dark gray and milky white. Finish and marble may vary. Also available as a console (2979) and cocktail table (2988).

Category: Tables\Accent, Side, End and Occassional Tables
ItemDescription: This round side table has a thoroughly modern base made from thin iron rods in a blackened finish. The irregularities on the iron surface are part of the finish and add to the sense of artisan craftsmanship.

Category: Tables\Accent, Side, End and Occassional Tables
ItemDescription: Minimalist hammered iron accent table with black wax finish.

Category: Tables\Accent, Side, End and Occassional Tables
ItemDescription: The Anvil collection was inspired by early memories of the anvil in the designer's family barn in Tennessee. The forged iron tops were inspired by 19th century cake stands.

Category: Tables\Accent, Side, End and Occassional Tables
ItemDescription: We love the juxtaposition of the industrial iron base, with the elegant and decorative top made of solid wood that has been scored and then clad in antique brass sheet. The brass surface will patina over time. Clad may vary. Also available as a console (2752) and coffee table (6175).

Category: Tables\Accent, Side, End and Occassional Tables
ItemDescription: Drum shaped side table with bronze aluminum base features asymmetrical honeycomb design cut-out design and clear glass top.

Category: Tables\Accent, Side, End and Occassional Tables
ItemDescription: Round side table supported by an iron base made from an interlocking scallop pattern and topped with rough hewn black marble accented with a ribbon of gold leaf banding.

Traditional design and mixed materials compose the clean-lined silhouette of our Theodore Dining Table. A round, gray solid marble top is fashioned to a tapered wood base that has been sandblasted in an ebony finish. The beveled edge of the marble top adds depth and dimension, while the dark stain of the finish accentuates the wood's natural textures. The natural composition and its height makes it a modern dining table. For a smaller version, see our Theodore Side Table (6852).Marble may vary

This 60" dining table is made of solid wood. The crisscross base has been stained a deep espresso color, while the top is clad in antique brass and textured to resemble a luxurious textile. Perfect as a dining table for six or a striking entry piece.

Category: Tables\Accent, Side, End and Occassional Tables
ItemDescription: This solid wood tabletop is diamond-scored and then clad in antiqued brass sheet. The looped pedestal base is fashioned from hand-forged black iron and cinched with a gold-finish iron belt. Scaled to hold its own next to a large sofa or chair. Part of the Draco collection. Finish may vary.

Category: Tables\Accent, Side, End and Occassional Tables
ItemDescription: The dichotomy of the heavily textured, cast aluminum base and elegant antique brass top adds to the visual interest of this unique design. Place it between two chairs so you can show off the oval shape and striking dark bronze finish of the base.

The collaboration of geometry, stone and gray finished wood creates an ultra-modern look. The tabletop is made of lava stone, an alternative to concrete that is lighter in weight. Featuring a lightly embossed texture and deep, geometric etchings aro und the rim, the top is finished in dark ash. The faceted base has grain textures, accentuated due to a sandblasted finishing process that has over 500 years of history. Built for dining, this table would also be perfectly sized for a grand entryway.

When it comes to fine dining, this table takes the cake. The entire piece is expertly crafted from oak, elegantly finished in a deep umber veneer with rich wood textures. The pillar design was inspired by the Modernist aesthetic of Brancusi, featuring stacked geometrics and craftsman-style turned details. Also stunning is the radial pattern in the tabletop, which makes this dining or entry table an even bolder statement piece.

Category: Tables\Accent, Side, End and Occassional Tables
ItemDescription: The elegant rounded tops paired with the reclaimed wood block bases create a bold statement. This round side table has a burnt wax finish on a dark waxed wooden base. Coordinates with DD2027 and DD2029.

The Brutalist style is often characterized by abstracted organic forms, with rough textures; and a dark, earth-toned palette. The slight irregularities suggest a connection to nature and handcrafting rather than the sharp precision of machine production. Also available with 48" and 54" glass.

Industrial materials and hand-applied techniques update the timeless shape of this enviable piece. A chiseled white marble top adds texture to the sleek, fanned black iron rods that form the pedestal base. Marble may vary.

ItemDescription: Bronzed iron rods create linear movement in this gridded side table design. Exposed brass caps sit atop the smoked glass top where the frame and tabletop meet. The glass has a subtle brown hue. Finish may vary. Also available as a cocktail table (265 9).

ItemDescription: This iron drum shaped side table features an antique bronze finish and repousse ringed detail on the top surface. Coordinates with Clint coffee table #4007.

A round top framed by a thick rim rests atop an exaggerated bell-shaped base, drawing attention to the sculptural aspect of the unique construction of the navy lacquer table. Artistic in form and functional by design, this piece would look just as brilliant next to a sofa as it would on its own. The versatile color of this side table allows it perform alongside various décor styles.

ItemDescription: Showcase classic elegance with this sophisticated accent table. ItemDescription: Showcasing an architectural façade of clean lines, the minimalist design of our Wenona Side Table works in almost any style space. The juxtaposition of the honed white marble top and the unique contour of the three-prong natural iron base plays on the symmetry of the shape's geometric characteristics. Upgrade the status of a room with this sleek structure. Marble may vary.

ItemDescription: Though side tables were originally made strictly for function, this modern maven delivers looks along with utility. Crafted entirely from solid oak, its seamless design is due to an ebony black veneer that's unique and rich with natural textures. Its function comes through in thoughtful details, like a wide tabletop, roomy nook and bottom drawer that opens and closes smoothly on soft-close slides. Features a signature aged brass pull.

For a full classic and subtly cosmic effect, gather with the matching cocktail table (6904) and accent table (6906). Also available in white marble. Finish and marble may vary.
